<HEADLINE>
POLKA AND KIELBASA 
</HEADLINE>
   (SUBS to delete first two items, on Bush-Clymer and Lieberman.
Bush-Clymer material is now part of BUSH-1STLD-WRITETHRU.)  
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   POLKA AND KIELBASA
</P>
<P>
   Dick Cheney danced the polka with a Polish beauty queen, spoke a
little Polish and dished out a few plates of kielbasa and stuffed
cabbage in Chicago Monday. Cheney, whose campaign style has
sometimes been described as aloof in recent weeks, shed his
motorcade and rode the El to the Taste of Polonia festival. At the
festival, he greeted the crowd in Polish. ``Sto lat,'' Cheney said,
or ``May you live 100 years.'' Then he spoke about his role as the
secretary of defense under President Bush. ``We were proud to work
with all of you to help bring down the wall and free the peoples of
Eastern Europe,'' he said, to applause.
</P>
<P>
   TUESDAY'S SCHEDULES
</P>
<P>
   GEORGE W. BUSH and DICK CHENEY: Allentown, Bethlehem and
Scranton, Pa.
</P>
<P>
   AL GORE: Louisville, Ky., and Columbus, Ohio.
</P>
<P>
   JOSEPH I. LIEBERMAN: West Peoria, Ill., and Mehlville and Kansas
City, Mo.
</P>
</TEXT>
