<P>
   CONGRESS-DEMS _ WASHINGTON _ As the Senate reconvenes, President
Clinton and Democratic leaders on Tuesday outline their
end-of-session priorities at the White House. GOP senators expected
to respond on Capitol Hill. (Mollison, Cox News Service). 12
</P>
<P>
   BUSH _ Republican presidential nominee George W. Bush on Tuesday
announced a $158 billion plan to help seniors pay for prescription
drugs, improve benefits and shore up finances of the health program
that ensures millions of elderly Americans. The governor's proposal
would pay at least one-fourth of the cost of prescription drug
coverage, whether seniors choose a new Medicare benefit or a
private plan. The elderly poor would get drug plans for free.
</P>
<P>
   Under Bush's proposal, health plans that participate in Medicare
would be required to provide a prescription drug benefit. Medicare
currently offers no prescription coverage. (Austin
American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-UN _ NEW YORK _ President Clinton arrives here today to
do far more than give his last big speech before a major gathering
of his peers, he also hopes to make progress on Mideast peace and
heal some wounds with Russia and China. Developing. (Deans, Cox
News Service) WAN: Location, Atlanta; Category, Religion;
Subcategory, Other.
</P>
