<P>
   GA-SENATE-MATTINGLY _ GOP Senate hopeful Mack Mattingly hung out
with some high-profile Republicans last week _ Dick Cheney in
Atlanta on Wednesday and Nathan Deal in the 9th District on
Thursday. He's hoping for some coattail momentum to help boost his
name recognition after having not been on the ballot for 14 years.
But wonks say he'll need more than that _ namely lots of TV
advertising to become more familiar with voters. (Pruitt, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   VETS-GORE _ At a recent party of his 24-member Sunday school
class, Jim McLaughlin decided to liven up the evening by playing a
trivia game, asking everyone to jot down ``what people aren't going
to know about you'' and drop the slip of paper into a hat. On his,
McLaughlin, 55, wrote: ``I did what Gore did in Vietnam.'' When it
was pulled, the crowd was stumped. Like many Atlanta-area Vietnam
veterans, McLaughlin, who's ``leaning'' toward George W. Bush in
November, is a little miffed at criticism from conservative
commentators that Gore was as safe over there as he would have been
in the states. (Hendrick, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS
</P>
