<P>
   TECH-OPTICS _ Some of the same venture capitalists and Wall
Street pundits who last year touted business-to-business Internet
firms as sure things now are singing the praises of optics. The
market has switched from being interested in what people will do
with the Internet to the plumbing of the Internet itself. Joining
with the monied chorus are companies positioning themselves to
profit from selling optic technology. But not everyone is convinced
that fiber going into the ground today will need the efficiencies
of optic technology anytime soon. (Brister, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 40.
