   STUDENTS-BASIC-SKILLS (Undated) _ Despite the efforts of
education reformers, American students today read no better than
they did a generation ago, and their mathematical skills have shown
just miniscule improvement, according to a new study of the
standardized tests known as the nation's report card, which have
been given since 1971. By Jodi Wilgoren.
</P>
