seeing sketchy evidence for a long-sought particle and must decide
whether to delay construction of a new, $4 billion machine in order
to pursue more evidence with its existing equipment. The lab is in
a race for the same particle, the Higgs-boson, with Fermilab in
Chicago. By James Glanz.
