French are once again being bombarded with books. Not school books,
but no fewer than 557 new novels, all published within a two- or
three-week period, all timed to coincide with ``la rentree'' _
``the return'' _ to work, to school, to the theater, to restaurants
_ that takes place en masse across France in early September. By
Alan Riding.
