<P>
   SCI-GREEN (Sydney) _ A worm farm in Sydney is among scores of
``Green Games'' projects _ from a solar-powered athletes' village
to roads &UR;  &LR; pitched so that &UR;  &LR; they channel storm water for recycling _
designed to minimize waste and resource consumption by the 500,000
people expected to converge here each day from Sept. 15 to Oct. 1.
By Mitchell Zuckoff. (2 takes)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-CLONE (Undated) _ Three years after the world learned of
Dolly, the cloned sheep, no one has taken the dreaded and
often-predicted further step _ so far as is known _ of cloning a
star athlete, dictator _ or even a beloved pet. But that's not for
lack of trying. By Richard Saltus. 1790 words.
