<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
 CHRON  
 Fall Entertaining: A trio of special menus to get you through  the
season   SAN FRANCISCO _  As the days shorten and the air starts to take on
a sharp edge, stoves all over the Bay Area come to life.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Fall is the perfect time of year to entertain guests. With that
in mind, we've asked two great cooks to produce a menu to suit
various lifestyles of Bay Area readers.
</P>
<P>
   _ If you want to spend time outdoors, author and television
cooking show host Joanne Weir has created an al fresco
Mediterranean-inspired dinner.
</P>
<P>
   _ If you don't have much time to prepare for guests, our
``Working Cook'' columnist Tara Duggan has created a flashy meal.
</P>
<P>
   Both menus take advantage of the season by incorporating some of
the best of what the harvest has to offer. And much can be prepared
ahead. Each author gives tips on how to do that, and how to come up
with a simply great dinner party, no matter which style you choose.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Michael Bauer, food editor &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
