<P>
   FOOD
</P>
<P>
   BANANA _ Building a better banana: My mother called long
distance last night. She was frustrated. She couldn't find any
decent bananas in two different store chains. She begins every day
with a banana. Mom's a trendsetter. Bananas are the most frequently
scanned item in the grocery store. That's one reason chains are
getting their own banana ripening rooms. Randalls has ones in
Dallas and Houston, with multiple chambers, from which where Austin
bananas will soon be coming. At its new produce warehouse in San
Antonio, HEB has a series of ripening rooms where they are working
on a variety of fruits in addition to bananas. The rooms are the
size of an 18-wheeler trailer so they can hold an entire load and
our testers do samples and taste tests throughout the day. What's
behind these new ripe rooms? The challenge of building a better
banana. (Crider, Austin American-Statesman) WITH PHOTOS
</P>
