and philosophy drawn from Taoism, Buddhism and the often unorthodox
ideas of founder Li Hongzhi, perform exercises during a
demonstration against Beijing's banning of the movement in China,
Tuesday. The demonstration took place in Midtown as more than 150
world leaders and heads of state were arriving for the United
Nations Millennium Summit. (Suzanne DeChillo/The New York Times)
