largest hospital mergers in New York City's history and in the
process became one of the industry's most high-profile executives,
was named president and chief executive of Aetna U.S. Healthcare
late on Tuesday. In Aetna, the country's largest health insurer,
Rowe gets a troubled company that is faced with the difficult task
of improving customer relations while raising prices for
managed-care coverage. By Jennifer Steinhauer.
</P>
