<P>
   BUSH-DRUGS (Allentown, Pa.) _ Gov. George W. Bush proposes a
fundamental overhaul of the 35-year-old federal Medicare program
that would encourage recipients to choose subsidized private health
insurance plans that include prescription drug coverage and would
also pay the full cost of drug coverage for the low-income elderly.
By Alison Mitchell. (We plan to move the story by 9 p.m. ET in
``p'' news file.) 1,000 words.
