   Top story:
</P>
<P>
   HMO-COSTS (Undated) _ Health insurance premiums are increasing
from 10 percent to 30 percent across the country, according to
employers, insurers and regional business groups familiar with
rates being paid by dozens of companies. Driven largely by
escalating drug costs, the double-digit increase in annual premiums
is the third in a row for many companies. The rising premiums
suggest that apart from the most restrictive, bare-bones HMOs,
managed care is no longer keeping medical costs down. By Milt
Freudenheim. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``f'' news file.)
1,600 words.
