</P>
<P>
   BUSH-DRUGS-COMPARE (Washington) _ Gov. George W. Bush's proposal
to redesign Medicare and offer drug benefits to the elderly puts
him squarely in line with his party's drive to reshape the program
by reducing the role of government, increasing the role of
insurance companies and giving elderly people more choices. By
Robert Pear and Robin Toner. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in
``p'' news file.) 1,300 words.
</P>
<P>
   With graphic.
</P>
<P>
   Reefer to GORE; story inside.
</P>
<P>
   RAMPAGE-ITHACA (Ithaca, N.Y.) _ In rampage killing cases around
the country, people who knew the killers often said they alerted
police about strange behavior beforehand, but were told by police
that their hands were tied. Ithaca, in a system that policing
experts say is unmatched in the country, has tried to deal with
this problem. When police here receive a report that someone is
behaving bizarrely, making threats or talking suicide, a police
officer and a mental health clinic supervisor are sent together to
assess the situation. By Laurie Goodstein. (The story has moved in
``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   Special Report: 2,400 words; with photo NYT20.
</P>
<P>
   INSIDE STORY PROMOTED ON PAGE 1:
</P>
<P>
   SANTAFE-OPERA (Undated) _ A curtain is descending, slowly and
gracefully, on a long stretch of the Santa Fe Opera's history. On
Sept. 30, just as the new concert season gets under way in the
world's arts centers, John Crosby will step down as the general
director of this adventurous company, which he founded in 1957 and
has run since. By Alan Kozinn. (The story has moved in ``e'' news
file.)
</P>
<P>
   With photo NYT7.
