 PERSONALS: High Calories and Hopes 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file.) &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; By LEAH GARCHIK &QC;  &LR; 
 &UR; c.2000, San Francisco Chronicle &LR;  &QC; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
The contenders in Family Circle's Third National Bipartisan Cookie
Cook-Off:  &UR; Tipper Gore &LR; 's Ginger Snaps vie with  &UR; Laura &LR;  &UR; Bush &LR; 's
Texas Governor's Mansion Chocolate Cowboy Cookies.
</P>
<P>
   Historians of baked goods will remember that  &UR; Hillary Clinton &LR; 
used to be known as the first lady who said she hadn't stayed home
and baked cookies, but when the gauntlet was thrown down, her
cookies beat  &UR; Barbara Bush &LR; 's and  &UR; Elizabeth Dole &LR; 's.
</P>
<P>
   _RepublicanShopping.com offers voters the opportunity to use its
links to Web sites that offer a cornucopia of products, each vendor
donating a portion of the profits to the Republican Party. This
means you could order Hillary Clinton's ``It Takes a Village'' or a
gangsta rap record, and a percentage would go to feed the elephant.
</P>
<P>
   _Although Texas executed six men in August, two in July, five in
June and seven in May, the state has only one execution scheduled
for September and one in October, reports the New York Daily News.
Three in November begin right after the Nov. 7 election, on Nov. 8,
9 and 15. A  &UR; George W. Bush &LR;  representative told the newspaper that
the scheduling had nothing to do with controversy that might arise
before the election, and that the dates are set by trial judges.
</P>
<P>
   _ &UR; Eddie Levert &LR;  of the O'Jays explained to Rolling Stone the
turning point in his deciding to support  &UR; Al Gore &LR; 's run for the
presidency: ``I've liked him ever since he started wearing the
short-sleeve shirts.'' (According to Rolling Stone, the O'Jays song
``Love Train'' is Gore's favorite choice for the not-yet-official
campaign song.)
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; BIRDS THAT FLY WHERE BIRDIES FLY &LR;
</P>
<P>
   TV broadcasts of golf tournaments have been using tapes of
birdcalls recorded elsewhere to prettify live coverage. According
to a Washington Post story forwarded to Personals by  &UR; Alice &LR; 
 &UR; Barnes &LR; , the sounds of a canyon wren (a bird never seen east of
Texas) were heard on the broadcast of the Buick Open tournament
from Michigan, and a white-throated sparrow, a species not heard
during the summer in the South, was broadcast both at the PGA
Championship in Kentucky and during the NEC Invitational in Ohio.
</P>
<P>
   Producers like bird sounds so much during golf, said  &UR; Leslie &LR; 
 &UR; Ann Wade &LR;  of CBS Sports, that they put birdseed next to
microphones. When that lure is unsuccessful, ``they have used a
(tape) cartridge at one time or another,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   ABC and NBC denied that they indulged in the bird &LR; - &LR; call fakery,
but the Post says some viewers heard out-of-place birds during
recent ABC broadcasts. ``It's deceitful and overkill,'' birder
 &UR; John Malcolm &LR;  said. ``Just how perfect do they want us to think it
is out there? Why not dub in harp music and rainbows for certain
crucial holes? Besides, it messes up our harmless little hobby,''
which is keeping lists of birds during golf tournaments.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; STEINEM HITCHED &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Feminist leader  &UR; Gloria Steinem &LR; , 66, got married at sunrise
Sunday, Sept. 2, in Oklahoma to entrepreneur  &UR; David Bale &LR; , 61. The
wedding was in the home of Steinem's friend, former Cherokee Nation
chief  &UR; Wilma Mankiller &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   It was the first marriage for Steinem _ who once said a spouse
becomes a ``semi-nonperson'' _ and the third for Bale. He is South
African-born, was an anti-apartheid activist and lived much of his
life in England. He moved to Los Angeles in 1990 and met Steinem at
a Voters for Choice benefit there a year ago. Bale's son,
 &UR; Christian Bale &LR; , is an actor who appeared in ``Shaft'' and
``American Psycho.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Though I've worked many years to make marriage more equal, I
never expected to take advantage of it myself,'' Steinem said in an
official release about the marriage. ``I am happy, surprised and
one day will write about it, but for now, I hope this proves what
feminists have always said _ that feminism is about the ability to
choose what's right at each time of our lives.''
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``I basically do what people give me. I auditioned for all &LR; 
 &UR; those weird movies and no one would give them to me. ... It's &LR; 
 &UR; always about the new girl. They're cheaper. Once you get your &LR; 
 &UR; price up _ and the parts aren't usually that difficult _ so &LR; 
 &UR; they're like, `Get the new girl, she's cheaper.' I used to be &LR; 
 &UR; jealous, and now I'm like, `Aw, you got a couple of more years.' &LR; 
 &UR; So you've got to do TV. You've got to do theater, you do TV &LR; 
 &UR; movies, you do commercials.'' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ &UR; Lea Thompson, &LR;  who's appearing in Chevy commercials and in the
New York revival of ``Cabaret,'' in the New York Observer.
</P>
