<P>
   SEARCH ENGINE: 09.06.00
</P>
<P>
   Site brings new meaning
</P>
<P>
   to term `moveable feast'
</P>
<P>
   The name sounds like the next generation of those infamous
``Road Kill Cafe'' menus dished out in recent years. That's not the
case with roadfood.com, a site designed to steer you to decent
dining while traveling. We tested the ``all restaurant types''
pull-down for Georgia and it came up with delectable stops,
including Blue Willow Inn in Social Circle (the ``must eats'' item
lists the fried chicken, fried green tomatoes, biscuits, greens)
and, naturally, The Varsity (the chili dog and frosted orange also
rate ``must eats''). Bookmark it for the fall and holiday travel
seasons.
</P>
<P>
   www.roadfood.com
</P>
<P>
   Jewish families get plugged
</P>
<P>
   in for Sabbath dinner
</P>
<P>
   Today's the day to order from koshersupermaket.com in time to
get it to your home, which they promise, by Friday night for a
traditional Jewish Sabbath dinner. This site is stocked with the
usual baby food, housewares and condiments, but it's the only site
we found with a kosher deli that offers four kinds of kugel,
tongue, brisket _ even chicken soup. The site's ready-made Sabbath
meals can also be shipped in a New York minute (overnight, that is)
to arrive before sundown, when observance begins. Speaking of
shipping, nonperishables are sent out on a flat-rate basis.
Overnight shipments can only be estimated at the time the order is
made.
</P>
<P>
   www.koshersupermarket.com
</P>
<P>
   Track the shuttle
</P>
<P>
   as countdown begins
</P>
<P>
   Today's Getaway tells you all about the upcoming shuttle
missions at Kennedy Space Center. This site is designed for those
who can't get away but want a virtual ringside seat to the launch.
Included: Launch updates, missing overview, weather and the
countdown.
</P>
<P>
   science.ksc.nasa.gov
